# AuroraWindow Pro

AI-powered hyper-local aurora forecasting and visualization platform.

## Problem
Existing aurora tools provide only global indices and static oval maps, but do not tell users:
- whether aurora is visible from their exact location
- how terrain, cloud cover, and darkness affect visibility
- where they should move for a better view

## Our Solution
AuroraWindow Pro predicts exactly where, when, and how well users can see the aurora.

## Key Features
- Live aurora probability map
- Hyper-local visibility score
- Topographic horizon check
- Substorm early warning
- Aurora chaser routing
- Photographer assistant

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: React, Mapbox GL JS, Tailwind CSS, Recharts
- Backend: FastAPI, Python, NumPy, AsyncIO
- Data: NOAA SWPC, Open-Meteo, NOAA VIIRS, SunCalc

